// =============================================================================
// L4-performance: Red-team Round 3 §5.1 — 1000-module load (256-module guardrail)
// =============================================================================
// @test: typecheck-pass
// @tier: 0
// @level: L4
// @tags: red-team, perf, modules, module-resolver, red-team-3.5.1
// @timeout: 60000
// @expect: pass
// =============================================================================
//
// Pins module-resolver scaling at 256 modules — 16x the existing module_fanout_bounded.vr
// guardrail (16 leaves), and the largest synthetic module count to date.  Production
// scale is 1000+ modules each mounting core.*; here we exercise 256 modules each
// declaring one type + one function, sufficient to expose super-linear cliffs in
// the symbol-table interning, mount-resolution graph walk, or per-module type-check
// driver without overshooting CI timeout (60s).
//
// **Audit reference:** vcs/red-team/round-3-perf.md §5.1.
//
// **Invariant being pinned:** the module resolver must scale linearly in module
// count.  Each module contributes one symbol-table entry + one type-check pass;
// resolver visits each entry once.  256 modules with no cross-mounts (independent)
// catches any per-module quadratic lookup.

